  "prompt": "Who is Margaret Hill Morris?",
  "response": "Margaret Hill Morris (1869\u20131963) was an American suffragist and activist who played a significant role in the women's suffrage movement in New Jersey. She is known for her efforts in advocating for women's rights, particularly the right to vote. Morris was instrumental in organizing campaigns, rallies, and other activities aimed at raising awareness and support for the suffrage cause. Her work contributed to the broader national movement that ultimately led to the passage of the 19th Amendment in 1920, granting women the right to vote in the United States. Morris's legacy is remembered as part of the collective efforts of women who fought for equality and suffrage during that era.",
